From 62b0ffc4a55420a91954ec7541d88d5ddc02f7e5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 13:47:30 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase A (rebuild): strip the custom diff stack
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The custom DiffEditorWidget-per-file + patch-reconstruction + custom
comment view-zone stack accumulated 30+ patches of complexity and finally
dead-ended in "TextModel got disposed before DiffEditorWidget model got
reset" on every line click after the LSP-upgrade attempt. The plan is to
rebuild on stock VS Code primitives — MultiDiffEditorWidget +
ITextModelService + the native Comments API. This is the strip pass
that clears the way.

Removed:
- KrtMonacoDiffView (custom DiffEditorWidget per file)
- krtPatchReconstruct (compact patch-derived virtual text + realLines map)
- KrtPrCommentController / KrtPrCommentThread / KrtPrCommentRegistry
  (Phase 9.5 native-comments attempt, paused mid-Session-A)
- krtCommentsView.contribution (Comments view registration)
- krt-pr-base:// / krt-pr-head:// passthrough providers (only existed
  to support createModelReference against the deleted virtual schemes)
- composingAt / renderInlineComposer / attachReviewCommentZones /
  pushReviewCommentsToController in the editor pane

Kept:
- KrtWorkspaceRegistry (Phase 8.6) — workspace folder owner/repo
  mapping
- KrtGitContentProvider (Phase 8.6) — krt-git:// scheme for
  `git show baseSha:path`
- KrtSwitchOps / KrtSwitchResumeService (Phase 8.7) — auto-checkout flow
- PR sub-mode, Tour generation, Storyboard layout (sub-mode framework
  still owns its non-diff DOM)

Diff sub-mode body, Tour mini-diff bodies, and Storyboard chapter diff
panel render placeholder text ("Diff view is being rebuilt on top of VS
Code's MultiDiffEditor. Coming back shortly.") so the surrounding chrome
still shows the file list / chapter list / graph / refs etc. Review-
comment loading still happens (so Phase C has data to push through the
new controller), but with no UI to surface it the comments stay invisible
until then.

Next: Phase B embeds MultiDiffEditorWidget in the diff sub-mode body
with file:// (modified) + krt-git:// (original) URIs.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
